oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Dug relics from Fairfax County, Va.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: These dug relics were primarily recovered from Fairfax County, Va. Items include: two pocket knives, an iron spur, two bullet pullers, percussion caps, a spoon, a French .69 bullet, a wormed Enfield bullet, a wormed .69 caliber US bullet, a knapsack hook, brass epaulet fastner, and two Confederate finials from leather accutrements.
oai_dc:dc.dc:format: Tools and equipment; Weapons and ammunition; Furnishings
